                            <comment id="13911076" author="mshuler" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 01:07:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After java driver jar is in build/tools/lib/ the debian packaging should install both the stress.jar and driver jar; patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13911710" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 16:48:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13911950" author="mshuler" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 19:42:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Needs copy to build/tools/lib/&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13912038" author="mshuler" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 20:47:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The artifacts target looks like the right place to add this, to me. Included a patch for just the build.xml addition.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13912115" author="mshuler" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 21:48:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removed my previous patch, as it&apos;s included in this one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since previous debian patch was committed, this patch goes back to specifying stress.jar, and adds a dh_install line for any jars in tools/lib/.  The artifacts jar copy to the -bin.tar.gz is also in this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13912123" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 21:55:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
